s:1962:"<p dir="ltr" style="text-align:left;"></p><p><strong>Overview</strong></p><p>HTML and CSS are the two fundamental technologies for creating web pages. HTML (Hypertext Markup Language) is used to define the structure of a web page, while CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to control the appearance of a web page.</p><p><strong>Course Objectives</strong></p><p>By the end of this course, you will be able to:</p><ul><li>Understand the basic structure of an HTML document</li><li>Use HTML tags to create different types of content on a web page</li><li>Use CSS to style the appearance of a web page, including fonts, colors, and layouts</li><li>Create responsive web pages that can be viewed on different devices</li><li>Apply best practices for writing HTML and CSS code</li></ul><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong></p><p>This course is designed for beginners with no prior experience in HTML or CSS. However, some basic knowledge of computers and the internet is helpful.</p><p><strong>Course Structure</strong></p><p>The course will be divided into several modules, each covering a different aspect of HTML and CSS. The modules will include:</p><ul><li>Introduction to HTML</li><li>Basic HTML Elements</li><li>Advanced HTML Elements</li><li>Introduction to CSS</li><li>CSS Properties</li><li>CSS Selectors</li><li>CSS Layout</li><li>Responsive Web Design</li><li>Best Practices for HTML and CSS</li></ul><p><strong>Assessment</strong></p><p>Your progress will be assessed through a series of quizzes and assignments. You will also have the opportunity to complete a final project.</p><p><strong>Outcomes</strong></p><p>Upon successful completion of this course, you will be able to:</p><ul><li>Create well-structured and well-formatted HTML documents</li><li>Use CSS to style the appearance of web pages</li><li>Create responsive web pages that can be viewed on different devices</li><li>Apply best practices for writing HTML and CSS code</li></ul><br /><p></p>";